sources.description:
Exploration of the Evolution of the Iconic Character James Bond 007 Through Various Actors and Films: A Documentary on the Journey of James Bond Across Decades, Films, and Adversaries, Highlighting Locations, Villains, and Bond Girls from 1985 to 2002

In anticipation of the 25th chapter in the iconic James Bond Saga, based on the novels of British writer Ian Fleming, Sabbatical Entertainment presents "For Our Eyes Only" an enthralling documentary that recounts and relives all of 007's menacing missions throughout this legendary cinematic franchise, from 1962's premiere of "Dr. No", to the highly anticipated "No Time To Die."


This Documentary has English & Portuguese audio, and subtitled in many lanugages

Director: Miguel Somoza
Writers: Carla Duarte, Miguel Somoza


00:00 Full Documentary with subtitles
02:23 Exploration of the evolution of the iconic character James Bond 007 through various actors and films.

14:02 The iconic journey of James Bond through various films and adversaries.

34:59 Exploration of the iconic James Bond franchise through the portrayal of Bond girls and key plot points.
42:16 Exploring the iconic elements of James Bond movies, from vehicles to weapons and romantic encounters.
